Class Export_mxJPO

java.lang.Object
  org.mxupdate.plugin.AbstractPlugin_mxJPO
      org.mxupdate.plugin.Export_mxJPO

public class Export_mxJPO
extends AbstractPlugin_mxJPO

The JPO class is the plug-in to export configuration items (administration objects) or in other words with the class the TCL update file could be created depending on the configuration item type (administration type).

Method Detail

exportByName

public Map<String,?> exportByName(matrix.db.Context _context,
                                  String... _args)
                           throws Exception

All given administration objects are exported and the related update file is returned. The administration objects to export in _args are identified by the administration type (see TypeDef_mxJPO) and the MX names of the administration objects.

The returned packed values (packed with method AbstractPlugin_mxJPO.prepareReturn(String, String, Exception, Object)) includes the logging messages itself and for configuration item type a collection of exporting information as map. The exporting information map defines three keys:

  • RETURN_KEY_NAME: name of the configuration item
  • RETURN_KEY_PATH: path within the file directory of the configuration item (without file name)
  • RETURN_KEY_CODE: TCL update source code of the configuration item
  • RETURN_KEY_FILENAME: file name of the configuration item

Parameters:
_context - MX context for this request
_args - encoded arguments from the Eclipse plug-in:
  • Map<String,Collection <String>>
    a map depending on the (administration) type (as key) and the related list of (administration) MX names
Returns:
packed return values in maps
Throws:
Exception - if export failed
See Also:
AbstractPlugin_mxJPO.prepareReturn(String, String, Exception, Object)
